# Joke Of The Day

A simple Android mobile application developed using the principles of Clean Architecture and following the MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel) design pattern. The app provides a daily dose of humor by fetching and displaying jokes from an external API. It serves as an example of best practices in Android application development.


### Technologies & Methodologies which used:

- Koin
- Coroutines
- Clean Architecture
- MVVM Pattern
- LiveData


### The App Scenario

Used the following REST API, develop a simple application that fetches the
Joke from the API and displays them in a list. The list has atmost 10 items and after 1 min, it will replace old one. 

The API is here: 
“https://geek-jokes.sameerkumar.website/“




### Supported Android Versions

android versions targeted:

-Android 5.0 (API level 21) or higher


### Used libraries

1. [GitHub](http://square.github.io/retrofit/) - retrofit
2. [GitHub](https://github.com/square/moshi) - moshi
3. [Github](https://github.com/casidiablo/multidex) - Multidex



